      <p>
        The scene is instantly familiar…a sparkling white beach with an unmistakable crater at the far end. Palm trees lolling lazily in the breeze. It’s the epitome of tropical paradise, the quintessential beach vacation. It’s Honolulu’s world famous Waikiki Beach on the island of O’ahu. Honolulu county, which includes Waikiki, is a city of over 900,000 people. But it takes up only about one eighth of O’ahu, the second-most northerly isle in the Hawaiian chain.
      </p>

